All Implemented Interfaces:
Attributable, DataDrivableResultRecordable, FunctionResultRecordable, Storable, org.apache.commons.jelly.DynaTag, org.apache.commons.jelly.LocationAware, org.apache.commons.jelly.Tag
public class HttpUnitSessionTag
extends SessionTag

This is a HttpUnit implementation of the @see SessionTag. It basically starts the application in the state provided by the baseUrl and beginAt variables and creates a new session for the function points to share. There is an extra property for this session to enable proxy support

  • enableProxy - Enable proxy support for this session ("true"/"false"|"yes"|"no")
Both of these fields must be supplied before proxy support will be enabled.

store

public void store(java.lang.String fName,
                  int event)
           throws java.io.IOException
Description copied from class: SessionTag

Stores the current state of the object to a given File. The default implementation of this method does nothing. Override this method to implement plug-in specific behavior. Some examples might be:

  • Saving the HTML from an HTTP plug-in during a state change or error
  • Taking a screen shot for a GUI application during a state change event

A listener is already registered for each function tag. All that is required is implementing this method.

Specified by:
store in interface Storable
Overrides:
store in class SessionTag
Parameters:
fName - the name of the if the file to store the contents to.
event - The event that occured (error, state change ...).
Throws:
java.io.IOException - If the state of the object could not be stored in File f.

setBeginAt

public void setBeginAt(java.lang.String beginAt)
Sets the ending path of the url to start at.

Parameters:
beginAt - - the ending path of the url to start at. For example, if the URL to start at is http://sf.net/projects/jameleon, then the baseUrl would be http://sf.net/ and the beginAt would be /projects/jameleon. This variable is optional This value is set and used from the context. In other words, this value can be set via an Applications.properties file or a CSV file.
